{
  "texts": [
    "We take this into account when calculating gender percentages.",
    "We provide bootstrapped 95% confidence intervals for the various diversity measures; in the case of gender diversity, the uncertainty of the name classifier is incorporated into the bootstrapping: the upper bound assumes all unknowns are women, and the lower assumes they are men.",
    "Data cleaning and homogenizing were also required for both language and production country metadata due to many non-standard and misspelled entries.",
    "This was necessary to be able to match them with standardized country and language names, which was required for matching with external databases, as described below.",
    "The international film festival circuit has been long discussed as a network in theory [4, 15, 52, 71], and described by borrowing terminology from network science, such as \"a network with nodes\" [52] or \"dense network\" [71]."
  ]
}